post_text:
Board of Education Seat Open:

Anyone interested in serving on the Webutuck Board of Education is invited to apply by sending a letter of interest that includes a brief description of yourself and why you would like to serve to the District Clerk by email at tracy.trotter@webutuck.org, or by mail to Webutuck District Clerk, PO Box 405, Amenia, NY 12501. Applicants must be a citizen of the United States, over 18 years of age, and a continuous resident of the district for at least one year. The individual appointed will serve until May 18, 2021.

Applicants must be a citizen of the United States, over 18 years of age, and a continuous resident of the district for at least one year. The individual appointed will serve until May 18, 2021.

shared_text:
Eugene Brooks Intermediate School
May 7 at 3:29 PM ·

We want to take a moment to recognize Makenzsilea Watson for earning a place on the 3rd Quarter Merit Role for EBIS. Unfortunately, we inadvertently left her picture out of the initial video created for the 5th Grade Class for those who also earned Merit Role. So, we wanted to be sure Makenzsilea is also properly recognized for her efforts. According to her teachers, Makenzsilea is also off to a great 4th Quarter, working hard from home and is making some great progress on an upcoming essay!

We are so proud of you, Mackenzsilea, and are happy to see you doing great things during your 5th Grade year!! - Mr. Pascale and the 5th Grade Team of teachers.

PS - we will work to highlight the achievements of other grade levels for 3rd Quarter performances in the days ahead...stay tuned, stay healthy, stay happy, and blessings to all!!

post_text: WHS Spirit Week Continues with Essential Workers/Super Heroes Day!

post_text:
Meet our very own hometown hero, Dr. Jessica McCoy, daughter of 3rd grade teacher Mrs. McCoy! A hospitalist at Phelps Memorial Hospital in Sleepy Hollow, Westchester County, Jessica was the 2007 valedictorian from Webutuck.
She attended Webutuck from K-12.

After graduation, she went to Siena College and then to Albany Medical College. She graduated med school in 2015 and has been at Phelps Memorial ever since. She is in the middle of this pandemic. Please join us in sending our thoughts and prayers to Dr. McCoy and her family.

We are so very proud of our hero!

In trying to keep the Warrior Spirit going, we will have a virtual spirit week. This will begin Friday, April 17th through Friday, April 24th. I hope everyone joins in on the fun. The following are the themes for the week:

Our days of spirit:
Friday 4/17 - Bit Emoji Dress Up day
Monday 4/20 - Superhero Day including our Essential Workers!
Tuesday 4/21 - American Pride Day
Wednesday 4/22 - College T-shirt or Favorite Team Day
Thursday 4/23 - Decades Day
Friday 4/24 - Webutuck Spirit Day - Put on your Webutuck gear!

post_text: Members of the Webutuck National Junior Honor Society recently enjoyed a special luncheon prepared by our cafeteria staff to celebrate their achievements. NJHS members must maintain a grade point average above 88, demonstrate exemplary behavior, and perform community service. This requires hard work and dedication and these seventh, eighth, and ninth graders put that effort in everyday. They were very appreciative of this well-deserved VIP treatment!

post_text:
If you’d like to help enhance Webutuck students’ educational experience, the QUEST Fund is accepting applications from students, teachers, administrators, nonprofits and community members. Projects may qualify for an award of up to $1,000. Ideas include, but are not limited to: independent study; new programs; extracurricular activities; individual creative projects in or out of the classroom; visiting speakers; artists-in-residence; professional development for teachers; scientific, athletic, or technical equipment; library resources and class field trips. Deadline is Nov. 8.
https://www.berkshiretaconic.org/bReceivebNonprofitsIndividuals/SearchApplyforGrants/TheWebutuckQuestforExcellenceFundQuest.aspx
